               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-242-person2013">
                  JOHN 
                  STANDFAST PICKFORD
               <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2013" type="surname" value="STANDFAST PICKFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2013" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2013" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Cross-street, Britannia-street, City-road. On the 4th of February I was in <placeName id="t18320216-242-crimeloc1365">Collingwood-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320216-242-crimeloc1365" type="placeName" value="Collingwood-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320216-242-crimeloc1365" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-242-off1363 t18320216-242-crimeloc1365"></join>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-242-off1370 t18320216-242-crimeloc1365"></join>, at near nine o'clock in the evening, there was a show; I heard a female scream Stop thief! I saw the prisoner draw his hand from Mrs. Cheeseman's side, make a stride, and run off; he was stopped by a neighbour, and given into my hands.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Are you sure you are not mistaken in his person? A. Yes, there was a crowd near him, but he was out of the crowd.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183202160088"></xptr>
            
