            . I am the <rs id="t18320216-242-viclabel1366" type="occupation">wife</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-242-victim2012 t18320216-242-viclabel1366"></join> of 
               <persName id="t18320216-242-person2015">
                  William 
                  Robert Cheeseman
               <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2015" type="surname" value="Robert Cheeseman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2015" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2015" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; he is a <rs id="t18320216-242-viclabel1367" type="occupation">printer's warehouseman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-242-victim2010 t18320216-242-viclabel1367"></join>; we live in Collingwood-street. On the 4th of February I was standing with my child in my arms, looking at the show; I felt the prisoner brush by my side - I turned to look at him, and put my hand outside my clothes and felt my money; I put my hand in my pocket to be more certain, and felt my purse and money - I pulled my gown over it; I then saw the prisoner by my side again - my child being heavy, I put my right hand to its back; I then felt the prisoner touch me again, and missed my money - I turned and looked at him; he walked one or two steps - I caught hold of him; he broke from me, and I cried Stop thief! three or four times; he got a few yards, and was stopped -I had 6s. 9 1/2d. in my purse.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Has the purse been found? A. No; there was no person on my right hand but the prisoner; there were a good many on my left.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-242-person2016">
                  THOMAS 
                  BARKER
               <interp inst="t18320216-242-person2016" type="surname" value="BARKER"></interp>
